org.trafodion.sql.udr

Enum PredicateInfo.EvaluationCode

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<PredicateInfo.EvaluationCode>
      • org.trafodion.sql.udr.PredicateInfo.EvaluationCode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<PredicateInfo.EvaluationCode>
    Enclosing class:
    PredicateInfo

    public static enum PredicateInfo.EvaluationCode
extends Enum<PredicateInfo.EvaluationCode>
    Info on whether a table-valued input or output column is used

    Note that these are not necessarily exclusive, a predicate might be evaluated in multiple places, although that should not be common and is not yet allowed.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      EVALUATE_IN_CHILD
      Predicate should be evaluated in a table-valued input before the data reaches the UDF.
      EVALUATE_IN_UDF
      Predicate is evaluated inside the code provided by the UDF writer.
      EVALUATE_ON_RESULT
      Predicate is evaluated on the UDF result, in Trafodion code.
      UNKNOWN_EVAL
      Not yet determined where predicate is evaluated.
